  "issue_title": "[bug] genie-health: health monitor never probes genie-api",
  "issue_body": "### Summary\n\nThe dashboard **Services** table includes a `genie-api` row (with `api_status_url()` after #164), but **`genie-health` never probes `api` at all**. `collect_endpoints()` only polls `core`, `llm`, and optional HA/nextcloud/jellyfin. When the dashboard is down on `:3080`, health history and alerts have no `api` row \u2014 operators must infer failure from other signals.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Stop `genie-api` while `genie-health` keeps running:\n\n   ```bash\n   sudo systemctl stop genie-api\n   # genie-health + genie-core still running\n   ```\n\n2. Inspect `crates/genie-health/src/checker.rs` `collect_endpoints()` \u2014 no `api` entry.\n\n3. Query health DB or dashboard `/api/services`:\n   - Dashboard may show `api` unhealthy (latency probe).\n   - `genie-health` SQLite `health_log` has **no** `service='api'` rows from the monitor loop.\n\n4. Compare with `genie-api` `dashboard_service_targets()` which **does** include `api`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- `genie-health` probes `Config::api_status_url()` (or equivalent) on the same interval as `core` / `llm`.\n- `health_log` records `api` up/down; optional alert path matches other services.\n- Default `:3080` config unchanged.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n`collect_endpoints()` returns only:\n\n```rust\n(\"core\", config.core_health_url()),\n(\"llm\", config.services.llm.url.clone()),\n\n### Hardware\n\nNon-Jetson (x86_64 dev / cross-build host)\n\n### JetPack / L4T version\n\n_No response_\n\n### GenieClaw version / commit\n\n`main` @ `crates/genie-health/src/checker.rs`\n\n### Relevant logs\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n**Suggested fix:**\n\n1. Add `(\"api\".into(), config.api_status_url()?)` to `collect_endpoints()` \u2014 skip or log if `api_status_url()` returns `Err` (https URL).\n2. Extend `genie-health` tests (mirror `core_endpoint_url_tracks_configured_core_port`).\n3. Optional follow-up: derive `llm` probe URL consistently (separate issue \u2014 LLM has no `[llm].port` today).\n\n**Files:** `crates/genie-health/src/checker.rs`, tests in same file.\n\n**Related:** #164 (dashboard api latency), #121 (core health URL derivation), closed #140 (api bind).\n\n**Real Behavior Proof (PR):** `cargo test -p genie-health` + manual stop/start `genie-api` showing `health_log` `api` rows.\n",
